The paper discusses a neural architecture that allows for dynamic reconfiguration of neurons to perform multiple computations, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE). The paper also discusses statistical classifiers such as decision trees and hierarchical Bayesian methods, which are topics that fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses psychophysical experiments, which could fall under the subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses timing phenomena, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV).
